      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-07-19</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-07-27T21:03:36Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Leadership PAC Prohibition Act of 2006 - Amends the Federal Election Campaign Act of 1971 to prohibit a candidate for federal office or federal officeholder from directly or indirectly establishing, financing, maintaining, or controlling any federal or non-federal political committee other than a principal campaign committee of the candidate, an authorized committee, a committee of a political party, or other designated political committee.</p> <p>Allows a candidate for more than one federal office to designate a separate principal campaign committee for each federal office. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
